Azure Virtual Desktop (AVD) is a cloud-based service that provides virtual desktops and applications to users.

Users can access desktops remotely from any device.

For example, employees can work from home using a virtual desktop hosted in Azure.

A real-life use case is remote work environments where organizations provide secure access to corporate systems.

Another example is educational institutions providing lab environments to students.

AVD enables flexibility, security, and centralized management.
